Why no permissive license: this repository's demo deployment bundles
derived artifacts (chunked text and vector embeddings, not the raw PDFs
themselves -- see deploy/huggingface/prebuilt/README.md) built from
third-party SEC filings whose redistribution terms this project has not
independently cleared for open reuse. Rather than attach a permissive
license (MIT/Apache-2.0/etc.) to the whole repository and implicitly extend
it to those bundled artifacts, this project stays unlicensed and
source-visible: the code is readable for reference, but not licensed for
reuse, until that question is resolved deliberately.

If you are interested in using any part of this project, please contact the
copyright holder.
